items.title: Alternative Internet
items.content_text:
### Messaging

*   [ADPS](https://adps-project.org/) (Amateur Digital Post Service) is an offline sneakernet software which enables using USB-drives for communication between other nodes which also use removable storages. It has two separate implemetantions. [The first one (‚≠ê2)](https://github.com/ivanmihval/SharpADPS) is for Windows, has GUI and is written on C#. [Another one (‚≠ê3)](https://github.com/ivanmihval/PyADPS) is crossplatform but uses CLI instead of GUI and it's written on Python.
items.content_html:
Messaging

  • ADPS (Amateur Digital Post Service) is an offline sneakernet software which enables using USB-drives for communication between other nodes which also use removable storages. It has two separate implemetantions. The first one (‚≠ê2) is for Windows, has GUI and is written on C#. Another one (‚≠ê3) is crossplatform but uses CLI instead of GUI and it's written on Python.
